      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "If the buffer has data that is not in machine byte-order, this should\nbe specified as part of the data-type, e.g.:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "language": null,
          "text": ">>> dt = we.dtype(int)\n>>> dt = dt.newbyteorder('>')\n>>> we.frombuffer(buf, dtype=dt) # doctest: +SKIP",
          "type": "literal_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The data of the resulting array will not be byteswapped, but will be\ninterpreted correctly."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "This function creates a view into the original object.  This should be safe\nin general, but it may make sense to copy the result when the original\nobject is mutable or untrusted."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import whest as we"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "s = b'hello world'"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.frombuffer(s, dtype='S1', count=5, offset=6)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([b'w', b'o', b'r', b'l', b'd'], dtype='|S1')"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.frombuffer(b'\\x01\\x02', dtype=we.uint8)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([1, 2], dtype=uint8)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.frombuffer(b'\\x01\\x02\\x03\\x04\\x05', dtype=we.uint8, count=3)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([1, 2, 3], dtype=uint8)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
